  return <MDXLayout {...layoutProps} {...props} components={components} mdxType="MDXLayout">


    <p>{`In this module, you'll see how we're using Redis Hashes to model the user and location data in our application.`}</p>
    <div class="text--center">
      <iframe width="560" height="315" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/xASSiToabSM" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture" allowfullscreen></iframe>
    </div>
    <h2 {...{
      "id": "coding-exercise"
    }}>{`Coding Exercise`}</h2>
    <p>{`In your first coding exercise, you'll be adding a new route that takes a user's ID and returns their full name.`}</p>
    <p>{`Using your IDE, open the `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`node-js-crash-course`}</inlineCode>{` folder that you cloned the GitHub repository into.  Open the file `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`src/routes/user_routes.js`}</inlineCode>{` and find the route `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`/user/:userId/fullname`}</inlineCode>{` which looks like this:`}</p>
    <pre><code parentName="pre" {...{
        "className": "language-javascript"
      }}>{`// EXERCISE: Get user's full name.
router.get(
  '/user/:userId/fullname',
  [
    param('userId').isInt({ min: 1 }),
    apiErrorReporter,
  ],
  async (req, res) => {
    const { userId } = req.params;
    /* eslint-disable no-unused-vars */
    const userKey = redis.getKeyName('users', userId);
    /* eslint-enable */

    // TODO: Get the firstName and lastName fields from the
    // user hash whose key is in userKey.
    // HINT: Check out the HMGET command...
    // https://redis.io/commands/hmget
    const [firstName, lastName] = ['TODO', 'TODO'];

    res.status(200).json({ fullName: \`\${firstName} \${lastName}\` });
  },
);
`}</code></pre>
    <p>{`In this exercise, you'll modify the code to return the user's full name by retrieving the firstName and lastName fields for the requested user from Redis.  `}</p>
    <p>{`First, make sure your server is still running, if not start it with:`}</p>
    <pre><code parentName="pre" {...{
        "className": "language-bash"
      }}>{`$ npm run dev
`}</code></pre>
    <p>{`Next, browse to `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`http://localhost:8081/api/user/5/fullname`}</inlineCode></p>
    <p>{`You should see:`}</p>
    <pre><code parentName="pre" {...{
        "className": "language-json"
      }}>{`{
  "fullName": "TODO TODO"
}
`}</code></pre>
    <p>{`Take a look at the `}<a parentName="p" {...{
        "href": "https://redis.io/commands/hmget"
      }}>{`documentation for the Redis HMGET command`}</a>{`, which retrieves multiple named fields from a Redis Hash.  You'll need to add code that calls the Redis client's `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`hmget`}</inlineCode>{` function, then place the values returned into the `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`firstName`}</inlineCode>{` and `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`lastName`}</inlineCode>{` variables.  You should be able to retrieve both values using a single call to `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`hmget`}</inlineCode>{`.  For guidance on how to invoke Redis commands, check out the code for the `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`/user/:userId`}</inlineCode>{` route which calls the `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`HGETALL`}</inlineCode>{` command.`}</p>
    <p>{`nodemon will restart the server automatically for you each time you save your changes.`}</p>
    <p>{`When you're ready to test your solution, browse to `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`http://localhost:8081/api/user/5/fullname`}</inlineCode>{` and you should see:`}</p>
    <pre><code parentName="pre" {...{
        "className": "language-json"
      }}>{`{
  "fullName": "Alejandro Reyes"
}
`}</code></pre>
    <p>{`If you need help from our team, `}<a parentName="p" {...{
        "href": "https://discord.gg/redis"
      }}>{`join us in Discord`}</a>{`.`}</p>
    <h2 {...{
      "id": "external-resources"
    }}>{`External Resources`}</h2>
    <p>{`In this video, Justin explains what Redis Hashes are and shows how common Redis Hash commands work:`}</p>
    <div class="text--center">
      <iframe width="560" height="315" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/-agsJUihrWw" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture" allowfullscreen></iframe>
    </div>
    <p>{`You can find documentation for all of the `}<a parentName="p" {...{
        "href": "https://redis.io/commands#hash"
      }}>{`Redis Hash commands on redis.io`}</a>{`.`}</p>
